A minimalistic digital illustration of a Russian nesting doll (matryoshka) made of sleek brushed steel and glass, the outer shell partially open to reveal a smaller identical container inside, which itself contains an even smaller glowing blue geometric cube at its core. The dolls sit on a clean white surface with soft shadows. The metallic surfaces reflect subtle gradients of cool blues and silvers, suggesting precision engineering and efficient packaging. The composition is centered with generous negative space, creating a sense of elegant simplicity and nested containment.
